&gt; Teltoli was shocked. Was this really the Carnage she had first met
&gt; when she had come to this planet for her first time?
&gt;
&gt; A dagger of fear twisted itself in her gut. Carnage didn&#39;t want her
&gt; as a friend? Well. She was going to say something to that!
&gt;
&gt; The Fuzor began to follow her again, from a few meters distance, but
&gt; just enough to let Carnage know that she was still keeping up.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;You think I&#39;m not Loyal? That I can be Trusted?&quot; She seethed. &quot;What
&gt; about in the time that we were here on Earth, the first time? Does
&gt; that mean NOTHING to you? If I wasn&#39;t a friend, don&#39;t you think I
&gt; would have joined the Maximals by now, instead of risking my life to
&gt; come here! I sought you out, tried to apologize, note the word TRIED,
&gt; and you shove me off like I&#39;m some dirt underneath your foot? That
&gt; I&#39;m not even worth considering?&quot;
&gt;
&gt; She took a couple of deep breaths, eyes wide with her anger. &quot;If you
&gt; would learn to trust the right people, then you wouldn&#39;t be run all
&gt; over! If I had of known you would be like this when I went away, then
&gt; I never would have left! Back then, Carnage, you seemed like nothing
&gt; could ever knock you down..&quot;
&gt;
&gt; Teltoli&#39;s voice had quietened, and her ears drooped with sadness.
&gt; &quot;You always seemed stronger than anyone I ever knew, even my Father.
&gt; I looked up to you, and anyone that strong would have been able to
&gt; cope&quot; She whispered, just loud enough.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;I&#39;m sorry that you think you get run over, but that doesn&#39;t mean
&gt; that I tried to trample all over you. I never did, and I never will&quot;
&gt;
&gt; Her anger had fizzeled out, for the most part. She never could stay
&gt; angry at people, for long, anyway. Her next sentance had a tinge of
&gt; anger in it, and her ears know lay flat against her head with
&gt; annoyance.
&gt;
&gt; &quot;But fine, if you want to trample all over me in your haste to
&gt; destroy what could be the re-start of a great friendship, go ahead..&quot;
